    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This specimen features the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting flawless boost transition at 4,500 RPM and exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The chassis remains rigid, retaining its signature 50/50 weight distribution and original double-wishbone suspension components with zero bushing degradation. Finished in pristine factory paint with a flawless interior, the drivetrain is rounded out by a crisp five-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential. This is a turn-key, collector-quality vehicle with no vacuum line leaks or thermal fatigue, representing a rare opportunity for the discerning purist.",
